QRTEA has traded at 10 yield until recently and now its at 25  Depends on your definition of high FCFE yield  Agree its not the right stock if someones looking for the standard compounder bro stock  But price is pretty compelling as long as retention thesis holds

Debt capacity is predicated on predictabilitydurability of revenues and QRTEA has 90 retention on existing customers  As an equity investor FCFE is what matters so long as you believe the company is appropriately levered  Diff story if you dont believe in retention rates

I have QRTEA trading at mid20s FCFE yield and midteens FCFF  Part of exercise probably has to normalize for the terrible HSN acquisition  NWC hasnt been normal since and its a huge drag on cash flow  Hopefully Liberty can do something smart with the cash
